Here is a sample web page layout that includes a logo, search bar, and photo gallery:

```
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Example Web Page</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="header">
      <img src="logo.png" alt="Logo" class="logo">
      <form action="search.php" method="get">
        <input type="text" name="query" placeholder="Search..." class="search">
        <input type="submit" value="Search" class="search-button">
      </form>
    </div>
    <div class="gallery">
      <img src="photo1.jpg" alt="Photo 1" class="photo">
      <img src="photo2.jpg" alt="Photo 2" class="photo">
      <img src="photo3.jpg" alt="Photo 3" class="photo">
      <!-- Add more photos as needed -->
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
```

In this example, the CSS file "style.css" is used to style the elements on the page. Here is an example of what the CSS file could look like:

```
.header {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
}

.logo {
  width: 150px;
  height: 50px;
}

.search {
  padding: 10px;
  margin-right: 10px;
}

.search-button {
  padding: 10px;
  background: #eee;
  border: none;
}

.gallery {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}

.photo {
  width: 300px;
  height: 200px;
  margin: 10px;
  object-fit: cover;
}
```
This layout provides a clean and professional look for a website, with the logo and search bar located at the top of the page, and the photo gallery below. Of course, this is just one possible design for a web page layout, and you can customize it further to fit your specific needs.
